- cs.AL (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the problem involves finding paths in a weighted graph. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper mentions the problem arising in computing shortest paths in optical networks. 
- cs.CG (Computer Graphics and Computer-Aided Design) is a possible category as the paper deals with paths in graphs, which can be used to model various geometric structures. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the problem arising in the context of robot motion planning.
